  "body": "The first change lets DESTDIR be used with `make install` to set the installation destination independently, as is required in Launchpad's build process.  See http://www.gnu.org/prep/standards/html_node/DESTDIR.html and http://www.debian.org/doc/manuals/maint-guide/modify.en.html#id459110.\n\n(Note that there is a possibility of some conflict happening regarding src/comp/back/rpath.rs, which relies on the prefix as a fallback path.)\n\nThe second adds a Python script to src/etc which can be used to grab the latest snapshots.\n$ mkdir dl\n$ CFG_SRC_DIR=. python src/etc/latest-unix-snaps.py\n\nCheers,\nKevin\n",
